        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Summary"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "GenAI cost forecasting requires a model portfolio because different workloads grow in different shapes. Linear extrapolation handles stable mature workloads; logistic (S-curve) projection captures new feature rollouts with a known addressable market; power-law scaling fits developer tools where engagement compounds. An ensemble blending all three \u2014 weighted by recent MAPE \u2014 produces more robust annual forecasts than any single model."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "bulletList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  "Always present forecasts as bear / base / bull scenarios \u2014 a single-point forecast gives false precision and no guidance on contingency budget sizing."
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  "Estimate the S-curve saturation ceiling from product data (addressable users \u00d7 activation rate \u00d7 sessions \u00d7 tokens) before fitting the curve \u2014 without a ceiling the model is unbounded."
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  "Track MAPE on a rolling 3-month hold-out and reweight the ensemble automatically \u2014 a workload that transitions from rollout to maturity needs the linear model to gain weight."
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  "Power-law exponent b > 1 is a red flag: cost grows faster than users, so a 2\u00d7 increase in MAU drives more than 2\u00d7 cost. Flag this to the product team before the roadmap commits to aggressive user growth."
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  "Revisit forecast assumptions whenever a new model tier is adopted or a major prompt redesign changes average token count \u2014 these are structural breaks, not noise."
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      }
